data.Name: WellboreID
data.Description: A unique wellbore identifier sufficient to create or look up a unique wellbore record in an OSDU platform.

data.Name: MarkerNameSet
data.Description: The name of the grouping/set into which this Marker Name belongs. Grouping may be related to may be relative to a geographic area, a project, a company etc. [def. derived from PPDM 3.9 STRAT_NAME_SET] Do not confuse with Marker Set Name, which is "WPCName".

data.Name: MarkerNameSetType
data.Description: The type of MarkerNameSet, such as vendor, scientific, working, corporate, lexicon etc. [def. derived from PPDM 3.9 STRAT_NAME_SET_TYPE]

data.Name: MarkerAbbreviation
data.Description: An abbreviated form of the marker name for use in situations where visually long and short names would be cumbersome, like when many are posted by respective well symbols on a map.

data.Name: MarkerShortName
data.Description: A name for the marker that is shorter than the full name but longer than the abbreviation, if necessary.

data.Name: MarkerName
data.Description: Common full name given to the wellbore marker denoted here. As opposed to FeatureName, MarkerName is more freeform, and may constitute a summary of other captured properties such as MarkerType, FeatureType, and FeatureName; "Woodford_Shale_Top" e.g. (As long as no reference object exists, this is freeform.)

data.Name: FeatureType
data.Description: A reference item describing the type of feature identified by the Marker, such as Base, Top, Sea Floor, or Oil/Water Contact, or other types of fluid contacts.

data.Name: FeatureName
data.Description:
The name of the Feature the marker is identifying. As opposed to the Marker Name property, whose format is more flexible, Feature Name should not combine other facets of information such as Top/Base, or lithology type. 

Feature Name would often align with a unit on a stratigraphic column.  (As long as no reference object exists, this is freeform.)

data.Name: MarkerStratUnitRemark
data.Description: A textual description of the stratigraphic unit generally (but not relative to a unique pick of the Marker on a well).

data.Name: GeologicalAge
data.Description: Associated geological age. (A consistent way of identifying this in OSDU is not yet defined.) This would necessarily be null for certain Marker Types.

data.Name: MarkerTypeID
data.Description: The category of stratigraphy or other type of observation along the wellbore, such as biostratigraphy, chronostratigraphy, seismic, etc.

data.Name: OrdinalSequenceNumber
data.Description: Sequence in which this unit occurs in the column, from surface to base [PPDM 3.9]

data.Name: MarkerActiveIndicator
data.Description: A true / false flag indicating whether this row of data is currently either active / valid (true) or inactive / invalid (false). [based on PPDM 3.9] This could be useful in cases where a MarkerSet file contains multiple interpreter picks for the same marker name, and only one of those is deemed to be "best-to-use" but the rest are stored for reference, for example.

data.Name: CertifiedIndicator
data.Description: A true / false flag indicating that the marker pick has been certified for use and is of long term value. [based on PPDM 3.9]

data.Name: ConformityRelationship
data.Description: A descriptor assigned to formation markers/picks that identifies the type of conformity relationship that describes the surface that was picked. May be "unconformity", "disconformity", "angular unconformity", "conformable" or "paraconformable". An unconformity is a substantial break or gap in the geologic record where a rock unit is overlain by another that is not next in stratigraphic succession. Normally implies uplift or erosion with loss of the previously formed strata. [based on PPDM 3.9]

data.Name: SurfaceDipAngle
data.Description: The inclination angle of a tilted planar feature, in degrees relative to the horizontal plane. It must be combined with a dip azimuth direction.

data.Name: SurfaceDipAngleUOM
data.Description: The unit of measure describing the value in SurfaceDipAngle.

data.Name: SurfaceDipAngleOUOM
data.Description: The unit of measure in which SurfaceDipAngle was originally measured when the data was first collected or created. (This may be the same or different from the current UOM. OUOM is captured because sometimes values get converted to different units making the OUOM differ from current UOM; OUOM can inform data users on possible causes of data quality issues, validating the source of data, and other data issues.)

data.Name: SurfaceDipAzimuth
data.Description: The azimuth direction identifying where the planar feature is dipping most steeply downwards relative to a horizontal plane. This is 90 degrees to the strike angle.

data.Name: SurfaceDipAzimuthUOM
data.Description: The unit of measure describing the value in SurfaceDipAzimuth.

data.Name: SurfaceDipAzimuthOUOM
data.Description: The unit of measure in which SurfaceDipAzimuth was originally measured when the data was first collected or created. (This may be the same or different from the current UOM. OUOM is captured because sometimes values get converted to different units making the OUOM differ from current UOM; OUOM can inform data users on possible causes of data quality issues, validating the source of data, and other data issues.)

data.Name: AzimuthNorthType
data.Description: The type of north reference governing the SurfaceDipAzimuth, such as "Grid", "True", or "Magnetic".

data.Name: AzimuthHorizontalCRS
data.Description: The geographic or projected horizontal coordinate reference system governing the SurfaceDipAzimuth. Must be consistent with AzimuthNorthType indicator.

data.Name: DominantLithology
data.Description: The dominant lithology (if applicable) of this marker pick. For example "sandstone", "limestone", "dolomite" or "shale".

data.Name: MarkerInterpreter
data.Description: The name of the Marker interpreter (could be a person, department/team, or vendor).

data.Name: MissingThickness
data.Description: The thickness of material (typically a rock formation) that was expected in this wellbore, but that is actually missing from this wellbore for geologic reasons. It should be recorded as an along-hole length in the wellbore to be consistent with pick depths.

data.Name: MissingReason
data.Description: The geologic reason why a portion of material (typically a rock formation) is missing from the real world material/rock being measured, compared to what was expected based on offset wells. Examples: fault, unconformity, fold.

data.Name: OverturnedIndicator
data.Description: A true / false flag indicating that the strat unit is part of an overturned section and that the normal sequence of occurrence is reversed. [based on PPDM 3.9]

data.Name: MarkerDate
data.Description: Date-timestamp of the date and time when the when the Marker was interpreted.

data.Name: MarkerMeasuredDepth
data.Description: The Measured Depth from a given Vertical Reference at which the Marker was interpreted or prognosed.

data.Name: MarkerMeasuredDepthUOM
data.Description: The unit of measure describing the value in MarkerMeasuredDepth.

data.Name: MarkerMeasuredDepthOUOM
data.Description: The unit of measure in which MarkerMeasuredDepth was originally measured when the data was first collected or created. (This may be the same or different from the current UOM. OUOM is captured because sometimes values get converted to different units making the OUOM differ from current UOM; OUOM can inform data users on possible causes of data quality issues, validating the source of data, and other data issues.)

data.Name: MarkerTVD
data.Description: The True Vertical Depth from a given Vertical Reference or Vertical CRS at which the Marker was interpreted or prognosed.

data.Name: MarkerTVDUOM
data.Description: The unit of measure describing the value in MarkerTVD.

data.Name: MarkerTVDOUOM
data.Description: The unit of measure in which MarkerTVD was originally measured when the data was first collected or created. (This may be the same or different from the current UOM. OUOM is captured because sometimes values get converted to different units making the OUOM differ from current UOM; OUOM can inform data users on possible causes of data quality issues, validating the source of data, and other data issues.)

data.Name: TrajectoryIDForMarker
data.Description: Specifies which directional survey or wellpath was used to interpret the marker, including the MD and TVD values.

data.Name: Qualifier
data.Description: Describes a qualifier used to describe a formation pick. For example not logged, missing, estimated or uncertain depth. [Based on PPDM 3.9]

data.Name: QualifierReason
data.Description: The reason that a qualifier was added for a pick, such as poor data, faulting, erosion. [PPDM 3.9]

data.Name: Quality
data.Description: The quality of or degree of confidence in the pick that was made, such as poor, uncertain, good, excellent. [PPDM 3.9]

data.Name: MarkerPickRemark
data.Description: A remark about a specific marker pick (not about the stratigraphic unit in general).

data.Name: RepeatMarkerIndicator
data.Description: A true / false flag indicating whether this marker is known to be intentionally repeated in this marker set due to circumstances such as folding, faulting or undulating horizontal drilling.

data.Name: RepeatMarkerReason
data.Description: The reason the marker was picked more than once in the same wellbore/marker set. For example:  folding, faulting, undulating horizontal drilling/geosteering, etc.

data.Name: Source
data.Description: The entity that produced the record, or from which it is received; could be an organization, agency, system, internal team, or individual. For informational purposes only, the list of sources is not governed.

data.Name: MarkerInterpretationMethod
data.Description: The method by which this marker was interpreted, such as surface sample, sub-surface, logs, seismic, etc.

data.Name: MarkersObservationNumber
data.Description: Any observation number that distinguishes a Marker observation from others with same Marker name, date.

data.Name: ExistenceKind
data.Description: Where does this data resource sit in the cradle-to-grave span of its existence? For example, Prototype, Planned, Actual, etc.

data.Name: PositiveVerticalDelta
data.Description: The distance vertically above the Marker position that marks the limit of the high confidence range for the Marker pick.

data.Name: PositiveVerticalDeltaUOM
data.Description: The unit of measure describing the value in PositiveVerticalDelta.

data.Name: PositiveVerticalDeltaOUOM
data.Description: The unit of measure in which PositiveVerticalDelta was originally measured when the data was first collected or created. (This may be the same or different from the current UOM. OUOM is captured because sometimes values get converted to different units making the OUOM differ from current UOM; OUOM can inform data users on possible causes of data quality issues, validating the source of data, and other data issues.)

data.Name: NegativeVerticalDelta
data.Description: The distance vertically below the Marker position that marks the limit of the high confidence range for the Marker pick.

data.Name: NegativeVerticalDeltaUOM
data.Description: The unit of measure describing the value in NegativeVerticalDelta.

data.Name: NegativeVerticalDeltaOUOM
data.Description: The unit of measure in which NegativeVerticalDelta was originally measured when the data was first collected or created. (This may be the same or different from the current UOM. OUOM is captured because sometimes values get converted to different units making the OUOM differ from current UOM; OUOM can inform data users on possible causes of data quality issues, validating the source of data, and other data issues.)

data.Name: VerticalMeasurementPath
data.Description: Specifies Measured Depth, True Vertical Depth, or Elevation. For Markers, the VerticalMeasurementPath will almost always be "Elevation".

data.Name: VerticalMeasurementType
data.Description: Usually, the Datum Elevation, in human readable form, from which the markers in this Marker set were measured, such as Ground Level, Drill Floor, or Kelly Bushing. (This should conceptually correspond to the the reference provided in VerticalMeasurementID.)

data.Name: VerticalCRS
data.Description: A vertical coordinate reference system from which the elevation for this marker set was measured, such as Mean Sea Level, Lowest Astronomical Tide, or NAVD88.

data.Name: WellboreVerticalMeasurementID
data.Description: References an entry in the Vertical Measurement array for the Wellbore identified by WellboreID, which defines the vertical reference datum for all marker measured depths of the wellbore marker Markers array.

data.Name: MarkerX
data.Description: The geographic map "X" value (aka Easting) of this specific marker pick. The MarkerXYCRS metadata must by populated to interpret these X, Y values. To know how this property was computed, refer to TrajectoryIDforMarker.

data.Name: MarkerY
data.Description: The geographic map "Y" value (aka Northing) of this specific marker pick. The MarkerXYCRS metadata must by populated to interpret these X, Y values. To know how this property was computed, refer to TrajectoryIDforMarker.

data.Name: MarkerXYCRS
data.Description: The geographic or projected horizontal coordinate reference system that governs the values provided in MarkerX and MarkerY.

data.Name: WPCName
data.Description: Name of the work product component, such as a short summary that identifies the contents of this work product component.

data.Name: WPCDescription
data.Description: Description.  Summary of the work product component.  Not the same as Remark which captures thoughts of creator about the wpc.

data.Name: WPCOriginalCreationDateTime
data.Description: The date that this Marker set was formed outside of OSDU before loading into OSDU. OSDU internally expects ISO 8601 date-time format.

data.Name: MarkerSubSeaVerticalDepth
data.Description: The marker's true vertical depth sub-sea, i.e., below Mean Sea Level. Note that TVD values above MSL are negative. This is the same as true vertical depth referenced to the vertical CRS “MSL depth”.
